ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a good option if your senior essay topic will not fit easily into the subjects covered by any of the seminars offered that semester. If you set up regular meetings with your advisor and create some deadlines for yourself (so that you aren't writing everything during reading week), it can be a very manageable process. It also lets you focus on your essay research without having to worry about other requirements that would come with a seminar (like weekly reading responses).
